## Fixtures

Place shared helpers in `tests/conftest.py` and `tests/fixtures/`:

- **`frozen_tracker(monkeypatch)`** ‚Äî a `Tracker` instance with `time.monotonic` patched
  to a controllable float; used across all APM calculation tests.
- **`event_sequence`** ‚Äî a list of `(timestamp, event_type)` tuples covering a mix of
  keypress, click, and scroll events across a 90-second span; used to test window
  boundary conditions.
- **`mock_listener_cls`** ‚Äî a `MagicMock` subclass that captures the `on_press`,
  `on_release`, `on_click`, and `on_scroll` callbacks passed to it without starting any
  OS hook.

---

## What NOT to Test

- Pixel-level rendering of the tray icon or overlay window.
- Actual Windows accessibility / hook permissions (these are environment concerns, not
  unit concerns).
- PyInstaller packaging correctness (validated manually or in a dedicated build step).

